title: What's on in Sydney: 20 things to hear, see and do this weekend
text:
Sarah Blasko will unveil tracks from her new album at the Graphic Festival on Sunday, October 11, at the Opera House. Photo: Jade Cantwell 
From retro music fun with Kiss to new music with Sarah Blasko, a Friends pop-up cafe and and tear jerker film Miss You Already, we have your weekend covered. 
Critics' picks by Elissa Blake, Sharne Wolff, Garry Maddox, Sarah Thomas and Louise Rugendyke. Send entries to shortlisteditor@smh.com.au
